## Health And Readiness

Every generated service keeps the same health surface:

- `GET /healthz`
- `GET /livez`
- `GET /readyz`
- `GET /startupz`

Use `/healthz` as the first smoke check after startup. The payload reports the generated service list so you can confirm optional features are actually wired.

## Deployment Notes

- Prefer `config/server.prod.yaml` as the production starting point.
- Keep SQLite and log paths writable by the runtime user before first startup.
- Disable docs or UI endpoints in production if they are not needed.
- Run `go test ./...` before shipping a modified generated project.
- Re-check `/healthz`, `/readyz`, and the expected optional endpoints after every environment change.
